    <div class="faq-column">
      <h3>1. How can foreplay improve intimacy in marriage?</h3>
      <p>Foreplay builds anticipation, increases physical readiness, and enhances emotional connection between partners. Taking time to explore each other’s bodies with gentle touches and kisses helps create a deeper bond and makes the sexual experience more satisfying for both.</p>

      <h3>2. Why is being present and mindful important during sex?</h3>
      <p>Being fully present allows you to focus on your partner’s needs and the shared experience, which strengthens emotional intimacy and improves physical pleasure. Mindfulness helps reduce distractions and makes every touch and sensation more meaningful.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-column">
      <h3>3. What are some ways to keep the spark alive in a long-term relationship?</h3>
      <p>Experimenting with new positions, changing locations, introducing toys, and exploring fantasies can keep intimacy exciting. Additionally, building romance outside the bedroom through quality time, appreciation, and flirting helps maintain passion and connection.</p>

      <h3>4. How does aftercare benefit a couple’s relationship?</h3>
      <p>Aftercare nurtures emotional intimacy by providing comfort, security, and physical closeness after sex. It helps release bonding hormones like oxytocin, reduces vulnerability, and strengthens trust, making the overall sexual experience more fulfilling.</p>
